{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"a16d7af7-abb4-4ebd-aaf3-2f5f155c8645","content":"Here are the **3 MSBuild evaluation performance anti-patterns** in this project:\n\n---\n\n### 1. Recursive wildcard glob (`**\\*.*`)\n**File:** `EvalHeavy.csproj`, line 9\n```xml\n<AdditionalFiles Include=\"**\\*.*\" Exclude=\"**\\bin\\**;**\\obj\\**\" />\n```\n`**\\*.*` forces MSBuild to walk the **entire directory tree** during evaluation. This is the single most expensive evaluation pattern—it scales with the number of files on disk and re-runs on every evaluation (IDE reload, build, etc.). Use a targeted path or specific extensions instead.\n\n---\n\n### 2. File I/O via property function\n**File:** `EvalHeavy.csproj`, line 13\n```xml\n<BuildNotes …>$([System.IO.File]::ReadAllText('build-notes.txt'))</BuildNotes>\n```\n`ReadAllText` is a **static property function** that performs synchronous disk I/O during evaluation. Property functions execute every time the project is evaluated and cannot be cached by MSBuild. Reading file contents should be deferred to a target at build time (e.g., `ReadLinesFromFile` task), not done at evaluation time.\n\n---\n\n### 3. Deeply chained `<Import>` files (3 levels deep)\n```\nEvalHeavy.csproj → level1.props → level2.props → level3.props\n```\nEach `<Import>` is resolved and parsed during evaluation. A 3-level chain increases evaluation latency linearly and makes the dependency graph harder to cache. In a real repo this pattern often fans out, multiplying the cost. Flatten the chain where possible—import only what you need directly.\n\n---\n\n**Summary by severity:**\n\n| Issue | Impact |\n|---|---|\n| `**\\*.*` glob | 🔴 High — filesystem walk on every eval |\n| `File::ReadAllText` | 🟠 Medium — blocking I/O during eval |\n| 3-level import chain | 🟡 Low-Medium — additive parse overhead |\n\nThe recursive glob is by far the most impactful. Fixing just that one will produce the biggest improvement.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"1b4709bc-0358-4e88-af8d-ae99b9a1ce27","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Now I have a full picture. Let me analyze the MSBuild evaluation performance issues.","outputTokens":557,"requestId":"1415:16A6CA:DFDE7C0:F95AFC6:69EC168B"},"id":"f81227a5-9c3f-47f8-8240-448447e74dd5","timestamp":"2026-04-25T01:19:21.400Z","parentId":"cc2cd2eb-8d1c-49f7-99e3-a2acd8c61770"}
